{
  "abstract": "It is said that poor soil fertility is a greater constraint to food production in sub-Saharan Africa than drought. Scientists of the International Crops Research Institute for the Semi-Arid Tropics (ICRISAT) have been researching the problem for years, and have developed simple and successful solutions to the constraints faced by smallholder farmers.",
